<HL>
   Carlson Cos. Buys
   51% Stake in Forum,
   An Australian Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6D
</SO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   MELBOURNE, Australia -- Carlson Cos., a U.S. marketing
group, said it has bought 51% of Forum Organization Pty.
Ltd., an Australian marketing firm.
   The price of the acquisition wasn't disclosed, but the
companies said in a statement that Forum has annual revenue
of around 20 million Australian dollars.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   E.C. Gage, chief executive of Carlson, said the purchase
allows the company to "rapidly expand its global network of
full service marketing facilities to its many international
clients and throughout SouthEast Asia and Australia." Forum
has offices in Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane and Perth.
</TEXT>
